title: Support Female Entrepreneurs
slogan_to_incorporate: United States American Women Entrepreneurship Cooperative
description:
About:
Inspired by the success of the African Women Entrepreneurship Cooperative (https://www.weareawec.org/) which has convened more than 800 female entrepreneurs across the continent, changing lives, growing businesses, and supporting economies, our organization has inaugurated a USA Women Entrepreneurship Cooperative to benefit women of all backgrounds (very diverse American cohort) whose businesses benefit the U.S. market. Please look at AWEC website above for reference.
What the USAWEC Program Offers:
We provide the highlights of an MBA curriculum in a condensed and applied format that offers
*live sessions with leading experts
*connect participants with business mentors
*encourage peer learning, networking, and collaboration as interlocking parts of the USA Women’s Cooperative experience.
Through this program, entrepreneurs from a range of industries, of all ages, with a minimum of two years of business operations will acquire business and leadership skills, leverage networking and mentoring opportunities, and grow their businesses.
About the Center for Global Enterprise (CGE) (https://www.thecge.net/) the PARENT ORGANIZATION of USAWEC and AWEC:
At CGE, we’re shaping the future by helping leading global minds maximize their impact. From applied research to bold community initiatives, we’re on a mission to make a difference by changing the way we think about global leadership.
The CGE was established to help educate societal stakeholders – as well as individuals from the private sector, the public sector, and academia – on the globally integrated economy and its promise for a better future.
LOGO OBJECTIVES:
The logo should emphasize the empowerment experienced by women in the program, the cooperation and shared learning, and communicate female power. It should also take into account the diverse American target audience of the program. Community/Support/Network should come through.
Also should somehow focus on this being a US program (compared to AWEC model which has an outline of Africa)
Requirements:
Logo should be consistent with CGE Branding- line, 2D, geometric, modern.
However for USAWEC, we would prefer a less corporate, traditional feeling and the logo should be consistent with an NGO or startup ambiance. Please refer to logo and graphics used on AWEC website.
Try logo with American colors (red/blue/white but not too Olympic-y)
other_color_requirements:
Color Palette: See above note in the brief please too. Other options:
Plum ( R:96, G:15. B:55) White, Black, Grey
